         For the above poster, It costs a total of 23 aa's for a wizard to get Manaburn while it costs a total of 27 aa's for a necro to get lifeburn.</P><P>Once a necro LB's he can die extremely easily.  A wizard gets the instant gate to nexus so can Manaburn then instantly gate out if in trouble.</P><P>This is one issue about Wizards that bothers me coming from a pvp server.  They can one shot kill anyone every two hours (fine, thats acceptable) but going even further, there is NO chance of killing them because they just insta gate.</P><P>In pvp, LB is a dangerous skill to use.  First of all, if you kill the person outright, you get no dot-heal affect.  Second of all, more than one opponent - you are a sitting duck after using it.</P><P>One on one LB might have it's uses.  A wizard however can run in to a full group of 60's, MB anyone of their choice, loot them, and insta gate.</P><P>Sure, insta gate to nexus is some added AA's - but that makes the Wizard completely unkillable in pvp. Not to mention Manaburn can do 7k+ NON crit.</P><P>We pay more for our LB skill, It does not do MORE than our hp other than the dot-heal effect (no use if target dies to dd) and we are suseptable to instant death after using it.  I'd say it's a tad overpriced myself.</P><P>Do I want to see these skills nerfed in anyway? NO<BR>I wouldn't mind seeing the instant gate to nexus on the same timer as Manaburn though.  Other than that I dont mind being oneshotted =).</P><P>EDIT: Just read that LB might be changed on Test, this has got to be the most horrible change from a pvp point of view I have ever seen. Let me use up all my HP then LAY DOWN?  How bout LB is followed by an Insta Harmshield to soak up that Heal?  Dont lay us down god.</P><P>Fermunda <Hate> </P><P>Sullon Zek</P><P>Edited by - Fermunda on 08/29/2002  18:22:31<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
