         Well I'm sure I could put alot of things in here that aren't practicle for LB but there is 1 thing that I don't care for with the skill.</P><P>Low HP agro!! WTF</P><P>Wizard can MB and yet there is almost 0 agro to it. Why is this? I might not be a wizard but by god I spent 9 points on a skill thats half assed at best and I die damn near every time. ( I'm not uber like some of you with a 90% survival rate )</P><P>The fact is LB does need improveing and the low hit point agro is a good place to start. Then they should move on to the dot component wich I do not believe will stack since another LB can not overwrite it.</P><P>Here is why I think LB will not stack with another necro even with DoT stacking implemented. ( Asumeing both necro's are lvl 60 of course )</P><P>NecroA and NecroB casts LB 1 second apart. NecroA lands first no problem. NecroB's LB hits but with no effect because the spell "Would not hold"</P><P>Now with that in mind if NecroA casts Vexing and NecroB casts Vexing they won't get any message stateing that their spell would not hold.</P><P>Just my thoughts on LB I know they are a bit jumbeled up, gramar is sub par and the spelling is awful, but just thought I would add my thoughts into this.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=12740" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=12740</a><BR><img src="http://boards.valiantelite.com/attach/necrosig.jpg" border=0><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
